No one ever really talks
about him anymore.

852
00:41:50.926 --> 00:41:52.176
Why?

853
00:41:52.177 --> 00:41:53.510
I don't know.

854
00:41:53.511 --> 00:41:54.887
I mean...

855
00:41:57.224 --> 00:41:58.390
Makes my mom sad.

856
00:41:58.391 --> 00:42:01.895
Charlie... well. he's just Charlie.

857
00:42:03.313 --> 00:42:05.522
I'm starting to forget about him.
you know?

858
00:42:05.523 --> 00:42:08.317
I... I don't really know.

859
00:42:08.318 --> 00:42:10.362
It was a heart attack.

860
00:42:11.446 --> 00:42:13.656
One day he was there.

861
00:42:13.657 --> 00:42:15.908
throwing me off the dock into the lake.

862
00:42:15.909 --> 00:42:17.826
hollering at me to clean the deck.

863
00:42:17.827 --> 00:42:19.161
teaching me to play poker.

864
00:42:19.162 --> 00:42:21.248
And the next...

865
00:42:21.957 --> 00:42:23.999
...he was gone.

866
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:25.418
And I miss him.

867
00:42:26.544 --> 00:42:30.297
Well. if you want to talk about him
with me. you can. whenever.

868
00:42:30.298 --> 00:42:32.092
Thanks.

869
00:42:32.801 --> 00:42:33.718
Mm.

870
00:42:34.552 --> 00:42:36.095
{\an8}I finished it.

871
00:42:36.096 --> 00:42:37.555
